{
  "texts": [
    "We computed the similar word list for each header by intersecting the list of other headers.",
    "For example, similar wordlists for the 'clinical history:' section include: 'indications:', 'history:', 'patient history:', 'reason for exam', 'reason for order'.",
    "In the later sections, we only utilize the 'finding' and 'impression' section from the original report.",
    "Noisy data generation:The most challenging aspect of radiology finding simplification is the lack of robust groundtruth, i.e., patient understandable summary, for model training while we plan to use the original 'impression' section from the radiology reports.",
    "To the best of our knowledge, no dataset of radiology reports and their corresponding patient-understandable summaries exists, and generating those summaries manually is extremely expensive and variable based on manual experience."
  ]
}